1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
The strongest model available to you may not fit
on the phone in your hand.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
But exposing a personal Mac as a generic remote-execution server
would be unsafe. NearBridge takes a narrower path.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
It is a native iPhone and Mac experiment for reaching one explicitly
selected capability on a nearby computer.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Both apps are user-launched. They advertise locally,
but a discovered device remains untrusted.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:42,000
The user compares the same six-digit code
and approves it on both sides.

6
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:51,000
NearBridge binds a fresh authenticated session to the paired keys.
Discovery never becomes authentication by itself.

7
00:00:51,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The iPhone requests contact with the Mac’s Primary Holon.
The signed workflow confirms one registered inert-text capability.

8
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:08,000
The Mac Host—not the remote question—chooses
which adapter can execute it.

9
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:20,000
I ask one ordinary, non-sensitive question.
It is signed, expiring, session-correlated, and input-bounded.

10
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:32,000
The Mac routes it to the selected OpenAI GPT-5.6 Sol
model-only adapter.

11
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:44,000
The separate app-sandboxed XPC request uses the Responses API
with store false, omits tools, and has no file, shell, workspace,

12
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Git, or device control.

13
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:58,000
The Mac signs the typed result. The iPhone validates sender,
session, expiry, signature, and correlation.

14
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Only then does it display the answer.
Both sides retain the same execution receipt.

15
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:19,000
The receipt records provider, capability, outcome,
acknowledgement, integrity, and latency.

16
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Sanitized diagnostics omit prompt and answer bodies
and redact credential-shaped values.

17
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:39,000
This is a bounded personal-AI bridge—not arbitrary remote execution,
payload encryption, or a production-readiness claim.

18
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Codex turned the security brief into incremental checkpoints,
native flows, isolated runners, and fifty-four tests.

19
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:50,000
NearBridge lets your phone reach a stronger nearby model
while the Host keeps control and audit.
